title: Heavy Rain And Wind Lash NSW, Flash Flooding Warnings Persist For Central Coast | 10 News
description: Heavy rain and strong winds have pummelled New South Wales, causing flash flooding and leaving homes and cars damaged.   The SES has been inundated with calls for help - and according to the weather bureau - the worst isn't over yet.  As we go to air, there are warnings for potentially life threatening flash flooding hitting communities on the NSW Central Coast. title: Severe Storm's & Heavy Rain Wreaks Havoc Across NSW | 10 News
description: Heavy rainfall over the weekend has caused widespread flash flooding across New South Wales.  Videos shared on social media show shocked Sydney residents as roads, gyms, homes and businesses were inundated following an early-morning storm that swept across the city.  The State Emergency Service (SES) responded to more than 1,400 incidents and carried out 20 flood rescues within 24 hours.  Several warnings remain in place for parts of the state as flooding continues and cleanups are underway. title: Iran’s Supreme Leader Blames US & Israel For Thousands Of Protesters Deaths | 10 News
description: Iran's Supreme Leader has spoken in public for the first time since deadly protests erupted across the country.  He admitted thousands of people were killed "some in an inhuman, savage manner" but refused to take any responsibility for the bloodshed.  Instead, Ayatollah Al Khamenei blamed Israel and America and specifically Donald Trump for the deaths. title: Rabbi Shot During Bondi Beach Terror Attack Speaks From Hospital | 10 News+
description: Rabbi Leibel Lazaroff, who was shot twice during the Bondi Beach terror attack, has spoken exclusively to 10 News+ from his hospital bed.   The 20-year-old from Texas tells reporter Samantha Butler how he took off his shirt to stop an injured police officer bleeding out, before being shot himself.   After 11 surgeries, he has now revealed plans to help organise next year’s Chanukah by the Sea at Bondi. title: Albanese Backs Down Over Hate Speech Laws In Bid To Salvage Bill | 10 News+
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has backed down over Labor’s expansive bill to combat hate speech, splitting it in two and removing the most controversial clause which would have criminalised the incitement of hatred.   The government is hoping this will salvage the legislation, as federal politicians make their way back to Canberra for an emergency two-day sitting to debate it.
